content: @Rob Hausam and I want to bring the following agenda item to the next meeting:

Structured Documents has agreed in principle to transfer ownership of DocumentReference to OO. However, due to its broad scope OO thinks that FHIR-I may be a more appropriate home for it.

  • If FHIR-I decides that DocRef fits better in the OO domain, then OO will vote to assume ownership of DocRef and follow up with FMG.
  • On the other hand, if FHIR-I decides DocRef fits better in the FHIR-I domain, then OO will inform SD so they can reopen the issue to transfer ownership to FHIR-I.
See this discussion for changes in docref scope: https://chat.fhir.org/#narrow/stream/179166-implementers/topic/Merged.20Media.20into.20DocRef.20for.20R5

related indirectly -- DocumentManifest will likely quickly be relinquished by StructDoc too. It is even less of a structure document thing than DocumentReference.. And I think DocumentManifest would be better managed by FHIR-I... (which might decide that DocumentManifest is really just a type of List, and thus remove DocumentManifest from FHIR).
Where is today's call @FHIR-I Co-chairs ?
